4:
Subaru?
Subaru, please wake up. You're
going to miss breakfast.
7:
Subaru? Are you there?
I'm coming in.
20:
Yes. I went to wake him up this
morning, but he was nowhere to be
found.
24:
That being said, we have an idea as
to his whereabouts.
26:
The lingering scent of the Witch still
surrounds Barusu. It is still
emanating from the place we found
ourselves yesterday—the
Kaleidoscope.
34:
As far as I could sense, yes.
However...
39:
It's hard to imagine Subaru would
go into the Kaleidoscope on his
own—especially without telling
anyone.
43:
You're suggesting someone may
have led him there?
47:
Yes... A mysterious power surrounds
that maze, does it not?
51:
I feel it would be unwise for us to go
in looking for Subaru by ourselves.
57:
Please, lend us your aid! Help us find
and rescue Subaru!
63:
Of course! You can leave it to
us—we'll guide you through the
Kaleidoscope. Let's get ready and
head over there right away!
67:
Strange.... All signs of Subaru have
disappeared from this place.
71:
Oh no... Could he have been caught
up in a shift?
75:
Wait here.
I will use my clairvoyance to look for
him.
80:
Clairvoyance? What do you mean
by that?
84:
It's my sister's special power—she
can see through other people's
eyes.
Any success, Sister?
88:
I found him. He's in a room similar to
the one we were in yesterday.
91:
Barusu is being held captive there
by a strange man.
95:
Yesterday? That would place it
somewhere in the midways. But why
would signs of him have
disappeared?
100:
Spirits, heed me... Can you hear my
voice? If you can, please...
106:
There's no doubt about it. I can
sense Subaru—he's at the end of this
passage!
116:
It's nothing extraordinary—I simply
borrowed power from lesser spirits.
If only Puck were with me now...
122:
I see. There's much about you that I
do not yet know—I'll refrain from
prying any further.
126:
Thank you.
Come, let's hurry and find Subaru!
130:
Tch... Of all the times for such
meddling...
138:
Nice of you to finally wake up, you
worthless brat.
143:
H-huh? Who the hell are you? What
do you want with me?!
147:
Hah, don't make me laugh. As if
you're worth doing anything to. I'm
simply going to send you back to
your original world.
152:
My... original world? How did you
know about that? Who even ARE
you?!
157:
If you wish to live, you'd do best to
obey me, child.
162:
(Hold on... If this guy's telling the
truth, this means I might have a
chance at going home...)
165:
(If I can just bring Emilia and the rest
of them with me...)
175: The Dark Mage of the Kaleidoscope!
179:
You've made me angry. Release
Subaru at once—while I'm still
feeling merciful.
184:
I have no time to listen to the likes of
you!
189: Give Subaru back to us, now!
193:
Everyone, calm down! If we just talk
this out, we can—
199:
My patience is at an end! Do not
interfere!
215:
I'm afraid that's as much attention
as I can spare you lot.
218:
O all-devouring Darkness...
O transient shadows that abound...
Grant me your strength!
221: Take care of these brats for me!
227:
Just hold on, Subaru! We'll rescue
you—no matter what!
